lead_paragraph: James Harden had 23 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists in his fourth triple-double of the season, and the Houston Rockets set an NBA record with 50 3-point attempts in a 117-104 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Friday night.

headline.print_headline: Rockets Take NBA-Record 50 3s in 117-104 Win Over Kings
